FBIS3-1128 "drafr054_c_94023" FBIS-AFR-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA ANC Midlands Official Reportedly Killed 20 Mar MB2103101294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0900 GMT 21 Mar 94 MB2103101294 Johannesburg SAPA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Durban March 21 SAPA -- Four people, including African National Congress [ANC] Midlands official and Richmond Youth League leader Mzwandile Mbongwe, were shot dead in Ndaleni on Sunday [20 March], police said. The ANC confirmed the killings and said it was investigating. Mr Mbongwe was a prominent ANC Midlands spokesman and was on the organisation's candidates list for the provincial legislature. South African Police spokesman Capt Henry Budhram named the other victims as Mr Mzo Mkhize, 22, Mr Mfaniseni Latha, 21, and Mr Muziwendoda Ximba, 22. Spent R4 cartridges were found at the scene, said Capt Budhram.
